  "prompt": "Where can you buy Lego blocks all in the same color?",
  "response": "If you're looking to buy Lego blocks all in the same color, there are several options available:\n\n### 1. **Lego Pick a Brick (Online or In-Store)**\n   - **Lego Pick a Brick** is a service offered by Lego that allows you to purchase individual bricks in specific colors. You can access this service online through the [Lego Pick a Brick](https://www.lego.com/en-us/pick-and-build/pick-a-brick) website or in person at Lego Retail Stores.\n   - You can search for a specific type of brick and select the color you want. This is a great way to get large quantities of bricks in a single color.\n\n### 2. **Lego Bricks & Pieces (Online)**\n   - The **Lego Bricks & Pieces** service on the Lego website allows you to order replacement or specific pieces, including in bulk quantities. You can filter by color and piece type to get exactly what you need.\n   - Visit the [Lego Bricks & Pieces](https://www.lego.com/en-us/service/replacementparts) page to explore options.\n\n### 3. **Third-Party Sellers**\n   - Websites like **Bricklink**, **Brick Owl**, or **eBay** are popular marketplaces for buying Lego pieces in bulk. Sellers often offer bricks in specific colors, and you can search for exactly what you need.\n   - **Bricklink** (now owned by Lego) is particularly useful for finding specific colors and quantities of bricks.\n\n### 4. **Lego Classic Sets**\n   - Lego offers **Classic Creative Boxes** that come with a large number of bricks in a limited color palette. For example, the \"Lego Classic Creative Brick Box\" includes a variety of bricks, but you can find sets that focus on specific colors (e.g., primary colors or pastels).\n\n### 5. **Wholesale or Bulk Orders**\n   - If you need a very large quantity of bricks in the same color, you might consider contacting Lego directly or a Lego-certified reseller to inquire about bulk or wholesale orders.\n\n### Pro Tip:\nWhen searching for specific colors, know the **Lego color IDs** (e.g., \"Bright Red\" is ID 21) to ensure you\u2019re getting the exact shade you want.\n\nLet me know if you'd like help narrowing down your options!",
